densworld_text: The weights are keys. The shape is the lock.
real_world_text: The map is not the territory.

densworld_text: A fearful observer sees landmarks in different positions than a calm observer.
real_world_text: The observer is part of the system being observed.

densworld_text: The dens is not older than you. The dens is contemporaneous.
real_world_text: There are no isolated systems. Every system is embedded in and interacts with an environment.

densworld_text: The cage is not the bird.
real_world_text: The word is not the thing.

densworld_text: Space is not a container. It is a relationship.
real_world_text: Space is not something that exists prior to things. Space is the set of relations among things.

densworld_text: The moat was an engineering project. It became an institution. And the institution became a way of thinking.
real_world_text: We shape our tools and thereafter our tools shape us.

densworld_text: They count the meters. They do not see the valley.
real_world_text: Not everything that counts can be counted, and not everything that can be counted counts.
The only way out is through.

densworld_text: At plural sites, two observers see the same landmark in different places—and both are correct.
The Archive is not preserving phenomena—it is destroying them.
real_world_text: The act of naming is the act of taming.

densworld_text: When you map the borders of the dens, you are not mapping something that was there before you.
real_world_text: Reality is not something you are given but something you participate in creating.

densworld_text: The boundary is not failing because the dens is encroaching. The boundary is failing because it sits on a slope we cannot see.
real_world_text: Gravity is not a force but a curvature of spacetime.

densworld_text: Human language captures shape data instruments miss.
real_world_text: The body knows things that the mind has forgotten.

densworld_text: The dens speaks in shapes. And so, unknowingly, do we.
real_world_text: We don't see things as they are, we see them as we are.

densworld_text: A thing with priority comes first and determines what follows. A thing with persistence merely refuses to leave.
real_world_text: Process is the fundamental category. Substances are derivative.
